  <a href="#1" id="1">
   The international community is starting to look beyond the conflict in the former Yugoslavia, and is becoming increasingly aware of the true magnitude and seriousness of ethnic and political conflicts in the former Soviet Union.
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   The problem is indeed a pressing one.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   The disputes in the Transcaucasus, central Asia, and elsewhere in the former Soviet Union are causing great suffering for those involved.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   If uncontrolled, they pose a variety of threats to European security, including increased traffic in drugs and arms as well as international terrorism.
  </a>
  <a href="#5" id="5">
   There are no differences about the need to resolve these conflicts: but there are differences over how to go about it.
  </a>
